<span id="freeTextContainer835599965898141463">Here we return to the world of <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10822858.The_Keeper_of_Lost_Causes__Department_Q___1_' title='The Keeper of Lost Causes (Department Q, #1) by Jussi Adler-Olsen' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Keeper of Lost Causes</a> with Mørck and Assad investigating the 20 year old murder of two siblings. This is a fairly dark and disturbing book and is not for the faint of heart. We have a group of entitled prep school kids who commit violent physical and sexual assaults throughout the entirety of the book. There&apos;s one girl that&apos;s involved with them and we spend most of the book trying to figure out just what the hell is wrong with her. The answer, when we get it, i</span>
  <span id="freeText835599965898141463" style="display:none">Here we return to the world of <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10822858.The_Keeper_of_Lost_Causes__Department_Q___1_" title="The Keeper of Lost Causes (Department Q, #1) by Jussi Adler-Olsen" rel="nofollow noopener">The Keeper of Lost Causes</a> with Mørck and Assad investigating the 20 year old murder of two siblings. This is a fairly dark and disturbing book and is not for the faint of heart. We have a group of entitled prep school kids who commit violent physical and sexual assaults throughout the entirety of the book. There's one girl that's involved with them and we spend most of the book trying to figure out just what the hell is wrong with her. The answer, when we get it, is both truly awful and extremely realistic and understandable.<br /><br />This is a very good book.</span>
